      formIIA: "“Blood has four parts: red blood cells carry oxygen using hemoglobin, white blood cells fight infection, platelets clot wounds, and plasma is the liquid that carries everything. About 45% of blood is red blood cells — that percentage is called the hematocrit.”",
      journal: "No journal entry required for this lesson (per the lesson plan) — narration carries the day.",
