        "Walk the sequence in order: mouth (mechanical + chemical breakdown begins, starch digestion starts here), esophagus (just a muscular passage, no digestion), stomach (acid + pepsin, protein digestion begins), small intestine (the main site of both digestion completion and absorption, helped by villi), large intestine (water reabsorption, fiber fermentation, no real digestion), and finally the rectum and colon for elimination. Knowing this order cold will make tomorrow's meal-analysis lesson far easier for both ages.",
